de": false}, {"name": "steal.static.views", "shortName": "function", "title": undefined, "hide": false}], "comment": " Steal is used to:\n <ul>\n  <li> easily load and compress your application's JavaScript files.  </li>\n  <li> switch to a different environment [development, production]</li>\n </ul>\n <h2>Examples</h2>\n<pre><code class='javascript'> steal.plugins('jquery/controller',     //steals plugins and dependencies\n           'jquery/controller/view',\n           'jquery/view',\n           'jquery/model')\n  .models('recipe')                     //steals files in the plugin's models folder\n  .controllers('recipe')                //steals files in the plugin's controllers folder\n  .resources('i18n')                    //steals files in the plugin's resources folder\n  .then('//path/to/file')               //steals files with paths relative to project's root\n  .views('//cookbook/views/recipe/show.ejs') //loads and caches a view file\n  .then(function(){                     //runs function after prior steals have finished\n     ...\n })</code></pre> Includes are performed relative to the including file. \n Files are steald last-in-first-out after the current file has been loaded and run.\n <h2>Concat and Compress</h2>\n In your terminal simply run:\n<pre><code class='no-highlight'> steal\\js APP_NAME\\scripts\\compress.js</code></pre> This will generate a production.js bundle in APP_NAME\\production.js\n<pre><code class='no-highlight'> steal\\js APP_NAME\\scripts\\compress.js</code></pre> This will generate a production.js bundle in APP_NAME\\production.js\n <h2>Compressing non-JMVC javascript applications.</h2>\n You can compress and package non-jmvc javascript applications by declaring your scripts\n this way in your html page:\n<pre><code class='no-highlight'> &lt;script src=\"file1.js\" type=\"text/javascript\" compress=\"true\" package=\"production.js\">&lt;/script>\n &lt;script src=\"file2.js\" type=\"text/javascript\" compress=\"true\" package=\"production.js\">&lt;/script>\t\t</code></pre> and then running either:\n<pre><code class='no-highlight'> steal/js steal/compress.js path\\to\\non\\jmvc\\app\\PAGE.html [OUTPUT_FOLDER]</code></pre> or: \n<pre><code class='no-highlight'> steal/js steal/compress.js http://hostname/path/to/non/jmvc/app/PAGE.html [OUTPUT_FOLDER]</code></pre> This will compress file1.js and file2.js into a file package named production.js an put it in OUTPUT_FOLDER.\n <h2>Run in production</h2>\n Switch to the production mode by changing development to production:\n<pre><code class='no-highlight'> &lt;script src=\"<i>PATH/TO/</i>steal/steal.js?steal[app]=APP_NAME&steal[env]=production\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n &lt;/script></code></pre> Your application will now only load steal.js and production.js, greatly speeding up load time.\n <h2>Script Load Order</h2>\n The load order for your scripts follows a consistent last-in first-out order across all browsers. \n This is the same way the following document.write would work in msie, Firefox, or Safari:\n<pre><code class='javascript'> document.write('&lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"some_script.js\"></script>')</code></pre> An example helps illustrate this.<br/>\n <img src='http://wiki.javascriptmvc.com/images/last_in_first_out.png'/>\n <table class=\"options\">\n                <tr class=\"top\">\n                    <th>Load Order</th>\n                    <th class=\"right\">File</th>\n                </tr>\n                <tbody>\n                <tr>\n                    <td>1</td>\n                    <td class=\"right\">1.js</td>\n                </tr>\n                <tr>\n                    <td>2</td>\n                    <td class=\"right\">3.js</td>\n                </tr>\n                <tr>\n                    <td>3</td>\n                    <td class=\"right\">4.js</td>\n                </tr>\n                <tr>\n                    <td>4</td>\n                    <td class=\"right\">2.js</td>\n                </tr>\n                <tr>\n                    <td>5</td>\n                    <td class=\"right\">5.js</td>\n                </tr>\n                <tr class=\"bottom\">\n                    <td>6</td>\n                    <td class=\"right\">6.js</td>\n                </tr>\n    </tbody></table>\n \n", "shortName": "Class", "tags": ["core"]})